main event: A witness observed six chrome silver objects in the sky for 5-10 minutes in Tampa, Florida on 7 February 1966.
interesting points: The objects were believed to be affected by cloud motion,The sighting lasted for approximately 10 minutes,The report indicates no discernible features of the objects,Only one witness confirmed the sighting, and there were no physical evidences or photographs recorded.
witness description: Mrs. Gertrude Collins, a 68-year-old housewife who appeared irrational at the time of the interview
